# ZakaatiFy üßÆüåô

**ZakaatiFy** is a personal **portfolio project** focused on building a modern, user-friendly Zakat calculation experience that helps Muslims understand and calculate their Zakat obligations with clarity, confidence, and peace of mind.

The project is currently in **MVP stage**, with most of the core frontend experience already implemented and actively evolving.

---

## ‚ú® Project Intent

Zakat is an act of worship rooted in precision, trust, and intention. ZakaatiFy aims to:

* Remove confusion around Zakat calculations
* Present financial inputs and outputs clearly and transparently
* Respect different scholarly opinions (e.g. Nisab differences)
* Feel calm, dignified, and trustworthy ‚Äî not overwhelming

---

## üöß Project Status (MVP)

This repository contains an **in-progress MVP built as a portfolio project**.

### ‚úÖ What‚Äôs Implemented

* **Homepage**

  * Clear value proposition
  * Educational content around Zakat and Nisab

* **Calculation / Data Entry Page**

  * Structured inputs for assets and liabilities
  * Real-time calculation logic on the frontend

* **Live Net Worth Display**

  * User‚Äôs net worth updates instantly as values are entered
  * Designed to give immediate feedback and clarity

* **Frontend Architecture**

  * Modular, clean, and scalable structure
  * Accessibility and UX considered from the start

> Roughly **70% of the frontend** is completed at this stage.

---

###  What‚Äôs Not Implemented Yet

These features are intentionally pending due to external dependencies:

* **Gold & Silver Price API Integration**

  * Live Nisab values (gold & silver) not yet fetched
  * Backend work is blocked until a reliable API is finalized

* **Backend Logic**

  * Zakat eligibility confirmation
  * Persistent calculations / summaries

* **Confirmation Page**

  * Final Zakat due breakdown
  * Payment guidance and next steps

---

## Why the Backend Is Paused

Zakat calculations rely heavily on **accurate, up-to-date Nisab values**.

Until a stable and trustworthy **gold & silver pricing API** is integrated:

* Backend calculations would be incomplete
* Final confirmation would risk inaccuracies

For this reason, development is proceeding **frontend-first**, ensuring the user experience and calculation flow are solid before locking in backend logic.

